教育經濟與政策
經三 選修 (0/3) 
本門課主要的目標在培育學生對人力與教育資源分配及教育政策等問題之分析能力。我們希望從經濟學的角度來分析教育之多面向，包括教育之市場、成本、投資、消費、經費、規模及資源分配等課題，課堂中並將對相關之教育政策加以剖析。
　

Educational Economics and policy
Junior Elective (0/3)
The main goal of this course is to cultivate student’s ability on analyzing 
human and educational resource allocation as well as educational policies. We 
hope to investigate the multiple dimensions of education from the perspective of 
economist. The topics of this course will cover educational market, cost, 
investment, consumption, scale and resource allocation. Contemporary educational 
policies will also be analyzed in the class.

兩岸經貿關係專題討論
經四 選修 （3/0）
兩岸經貿關係是台灣經濟發展的關鍵影響因素。本課程以專題討論方式協助學生瞭解兩岸經貿發展的趨勢及相關課題，課程內容涵蓋：
1. 中國大陸經濟趨勢及對台灣的影響
2. 兩岸經貿發展及相關課題
3. 兩岸貿易及台商大陸投資
4. 兩岸協商與兩岸經貿關係正常化
5. 兩岸經濟合作架構協議（ECFA）相關課題
6. 兩岸經貿關係發展的非經濟因素
　

Topics on Cross-Strait Economic 
Relations 
Senior Elective (3/0)
The cross-strait economic relations are the most decisive influence on Taiwan’s 
economic development. This course is designed to assist students to understand 
the trends of cross-strait economic relations and related issues. Followings are 
contents of this course:
1. The trend of China’s economy and its impact on Taiwan
2. The development of cross-strait economic relations and related issues
3. The cross-strait trade and Taiwanese investment in China
4. Cross-strait negotiations and normalization on cross-strait economic 
relations
5. Related issues on ECFA (Cross-Strait Economic Cooperation Framework 
Agreement) 
6. Non-economic factors behind cross-strait economic relations
　

國際經濟學  


經四A  必修  
(3 - 3)  


本課程講授國際經濟學重要理論及當前國際金融問題，包括國際貿易理論與政策，及國際金融兩部分，前者涵蓋國際貿易理論、經濟成長與國際貿易、貿易政策，後者涵蓋國際收支平衡表、外匯市場、匯率的決定理論、固定匯率與浮動匯率制度下的總體經濟政策、開放經濟體系物價與產出、最適通貨區域、國際金融市場與工具，以及國際貨幣制度。

 

INTERNATIONAL ECONOMICS


Senior  required  (3-3)

This course provides the major theories in international economics 
and current international financial issues. It comprises international trade 
theory and policy, and international finance. The former covers the 
international trade theories, economic growth and international trade, and 
international trade policy. The latter covers balance of payments account, 
foreign exchange market, exchange rates determination, macroeconomic policy 
under the fixed and flexible exchange system, output and price in the open 
economy, optimum currency area, international financial markets and instruments, 
and current international monetary arrangements. 


 

 

國際經濟學  


經四B、C 
必修  (3 ─ 3)  


本課程旨在講授國際經濟學重要理論及問題，期使學生瞭解並評估國際經濟現況。教學內容包括國際貿易與國際金融兩部分，其中國際貿易討論國際貿易理論、經濟成長與國際貿易、貿易政策，國際金融則探討外匯市場、匯率的決定、浮動匯率制度下的總體經濟政策與調整、最適通貨區域與歐洲經驗、國際資本市場、開發中國家債務問題等主題。此外，如何將國際經濟理論應用在現實主要國際經濟問題之分析亦是本課程主要特色之一。

INTERNATIONAL ECONOMICS


Senior  required  (3-3)

    This course mainly provides the most important theories and an 
up-to-date analytical framework on international economics for illuminating 
current events.  It is divided into two halves, a one-semester course on trade 
theory and a one-semester course on international monetary economics.

    The course on trade theory covers international trade theories, 
economic growth and international economics, international trade policy.

    International monetary economics covers several topics 
including (1)exchange rates and the foreign exchange market, (2) exchange rates 
determination, (3)macroeconomic policy and coordination under floating exchange 
rates, (4)optimum currency areas and the European experience, (5)global capital 
market, (6)debt problem in developing countries.


    The application of international economics in current events is also 
emphasized in this course.


 

管理經濟學  


經四  選修  
(2 - 2)  


本科目主要在探討如何將個體經濟理論應用在消費者行為分析和企業經營決策上，結合經濟理論及統計計量的分析，探討如何有效解決企業面對的問題，幫助學生熟悉經濟概念並靈活的運用在不同產業結構下廠商的決策分析。


 


MANAGERIAL ECONOMICS

Senior elective  (2 - 2)

Managerial Economics brings together topics in microeconomics that 
can be applied to business decision making in various market structures. The 
objective of Managerial Economics is to help students understand and predict the 
economic forces shaping real-world business decisions and develop overall 
analytical skills of student.


 

勞動經濟學  


經四  選修  
(2 -2)  


本課程著重理論與實務的討論，先回顧勞動市場的現象，再試圖以理論來解釋。包含的主題有勞動供給、勞動需求、勞動均衡、補償薪資差異、人力資本投資、勞動力遷徙、勞動市場歧視與工作動機。

LABOR ECONOMICS

Senior elective (2 - 2)

This course reviews stylized 
facts in labor markets and tries to use theories to explain these facts. Topics 
discussed include labor supply, labor demand, labor market equilibrium, wage 
differential, human capital and investment, labor mobility, labor market 
discrimination, and work incentives.

 


貨幣理論與政策

經四 
選修  (2 -2)  


1.  
貨幣理論與政策之簡介


2.  
古典學派與凱因斯學派之比較


3.  
各種貨幣需求理論之分析


4.  
各種貨幣供給理論之分析


5.  
凱因斯學派的改革論點


6.  
凱因斯一般理論的貨幣理論

 

Monetary Theory and Policy

Senior elective (2 - 2)


1.    
An Introduction to Monetary 
Theory and Policy.


2.    
The Static Classical and 
Keynesian Models.


3.    
The Theories of Demand for Money.


4.    
The Theories of Supply for Money.


5.    
The Keynesian Revolutions.


6.    
The Keynes’ General Theory as 
Monetary Theory

 


商業銀行經營  

經四  選修  
(2 -2)  


本課程係探討商業銀行的產品、金融法令政策及經營與管理，並研究個人信託與法人信託的發展。除了書本上理論的探討外，並就實際的營運現象予以研究，期使學員能對商業銀行業務有更深層的認識與瞭解。
　


THE MANAGEMENT OF COMMERCIAL 
BANKING

Senior elective (2 - 2)

This course researches 
into the commercial bank products, government regulation policies and bank 
operation and management. It also researches into the development of the 
personal trust and corporate trust. Not only discussed the theory in the book 
but also studied the operating phenomenon in practice, so that students could 
get deeper insights and understandings of commercial banking business.

 

國際政治經濟學 


經四  選修  
(2 - 2)  


本科目旨在探討國際經濟與國際政治之互動,涵蓋項目包括:國際政治經濟體系，國際政治經濟學之研究取徑,援外政策，經濟製裁，外人投資，智慧財產權,貿易政策之決定理論,國際合作｡

 

INTERNATIONAL POLITICAL ECONOMICS

Senior elective (2 - 2)

This course is aimed at the exploration on the interactions between 
international economy and international politics. Subjects covered include 
system of international political economy, research approaches to international 
political economy, foreign aid, economic sanction, foreign investment, 
intellectual property rights, trade policies, and international cooperation.

 

產業經濟學  


經四  選修  
(2 - 2) 
產業經濟學下學期的課程重點在於賽局理論，利用賽局理論的觀點探討廠商間的兢爭關係。
我們所熟知的廠商競爭策略有數量競爭、價格競爭以及非價格競爭。廠商之間的非價格競爭包括：廣告、研發以及專利權等，上述的議題我們透過Cournot模型、Bertrand模型以及Hotelling模型加以介紹。廠商間除了競爭的議題外，尚有水平整合與垂直整合的議題。目前臺灣的銀行業正在整合的工作，其整合屬於水平整合，整合後的效果為何？我們可以由產業經濟理論洞燭先機。

總之，本課程除產業經濟理論的介紹外，更希望將理論與實務結合。


Industrial Economics (Undergraduate) 

Senior elective (2 - 2)

During second semester, we put a key point on 
game theory in this course (Industrial Economics).  We discuss a competitive 
relationship among firms by game theory.

The firms’ competitive strategies have quantity competition, 
price competition and non-price competition.  The non-price competition involves 
advertisements, R&D and patents, etc.  We use Cournot model, Bertrand model and 
Hotelling model to introduce about mentioned issues.  Besides a competitive 
issue, we will also discuss the issues of horizontal merger and vertical 
merger.  The bank industry in Taiwan is engaged in a job of merger.  It belongs 
to a horizontal merger.  We are interested that what the effect is after 
merger?  We may get some viewpoints using the industrial economics theory.

To sum up, besides the industrial economics theory involves in 
this course, we also hope that the theory and the practice could be combined.

 

法律經濟學

經四  選修  
(2 - 2)  


法律是有國家強制力為後盾的行為規範。除了維護正義之外，法律還可以在社會上發揮下列功能：1.作為改變行為的誘因以及2.作為追求政策目標的工具。法律經濟學是科際整合性領域。本課程以經濟學決策分析為工具，研究1.不同規範可能造成人們不同的行為反應；以及2.規範應如何設計以達成某政策目標。授課內容包含：財產權法，契約法、侵權法等相關議題之經濟分析。

 

LAW AND ECONOMICS

Senior elective  (2-2)

Law is behavior rule enforced by state sanction system. Besides 
pursuing social justice, law can serve other purposes such as 1. providing 
incentives for changing behavior, and 2. providing instruments to pursue policy 
objectives. This course is an interdisciplinary study. With economic analysis as 
tools, we study 1.People’s behavioral responses to different rules, and 2. How 
should the rules be designed to achieve social goals? This course covers the 
economic analysis of property law, contract law and tort law 

 

國際經濟專題討論  


經四 選修 （2-2） 


本課程為兩學期國際經濟專題討論課程，將對國際金融理論提供一個具有系統性的架構。上學期課程中，首先要討論國際收支帳的問題，同時也將介紹外匯市場與貿易彈性；其次要探討國民所得與貿易收支；接著則說明總體支出、匯率與政策搭配的問題，而貨幣、物價與國際收支之間的關係亦將在此部分予以討論。最後分析小型開放經濟體系的非貿易財模型。下學期的課程中，首先要討論國際資本不完全移動下的Mundell-Fleming模型，同時也將介紹國際資本完全移動下的總體經濟政策效果；其次要探討金融市場危機；接著則說明在國際間的政策協調問題，而總合供給與通貨膨脹之間的關係亦將在此部分予以討論。最後分析預期、貨幣與匯率之間的關聯性。

 

Seminar 
on international economics

Senior elective  (2-2)

This course is a two-semester sequence seminar in 
international economics. It focuses on international money and finance in an 
academic year. 

In the first semester of this course, we start with a detailed 
analysis of the balance of payments accounts. A description of the foreign 
exchange market and trade elasticities in the second part. The third part 
introduce the national income and the  trade balance. In the fourth part, the 
issues of spending, exchange rate and policy assignment will be discussed. In 
addition, we will incorporate money supply, price level and the balance of 
payment. The small open economies with non-traded goods will be introduced in 
the final part.

In the second semester of this course, we start with a 
detailed analysis of the Mundell-Fleming model with partial international 
capital mobility. A description of fiscal and monetary polices under modern 
financial market conditions in the second part. The third part introduce the 
crises in emerging markets. In the fourth part, the issues of interdependence 
and policy coordination will be discussed. In addition, we will incorporate 
supply, inflation, expectations, monetary and foreign exchange rate in the final 
part.

 

政治經濟學

經四  選修  
(2 - 2)  


政治經濟學旨在探討國家或政府對經濟的乾預和後果。本課程將以前現代／現代／後現代為基本架構，討論國家、經濟、生產方式、消費形態、相關政策、文化現象、全球化的政治經濟特性等課題。本學年上學期將包括下列之主題和進度：（一）政治和政策的思考模型；（二）現代國家和現代經濟的形成；（三）現代大眾生產方式（福特主義）的形成和現代大眾消費之特性；預算和外貿政策之特性。本學年下學期的主題和進度︰（一）社會福利、環保、後冷戰時期的國防和國安政策；（二）後福特主義、後工業社會、後現代社會；（三）文化現象和文化創意產業；（四）全球化和「金磚四國」的啟示。


International Political Economics

Senior elective  (2-2)

The main theme of Political 
Economy is to explore the impacts and consequences of state on economic affairs. 
Accordingly, in the time frame of per-modern, modern, and post-modern, this 
course will discuss the nature of state, the formation of modern economy, the 
ways of industrial production (Fordism and industrialism), consumerism and 
culture phenomena. , some related political-economic policies, and globalization 
in terms of BRICs. 
　



國立交通大學機構典藏：運用Dunning 的折衷理論分析台灣電子製造廠商赴大陸直接投資決策
































































